==English==

===Etymology===
Ultimately from the Latin ''[[tendere]]'' / ''[[tendo#Latin|tendō]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-tendency.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|tendencies}}

# A [[likelihood]] of behaving in a particular way or going in a particular direction; a [[tending]] toward.
#: ''Denim has a '''tendency''' to fade.''
# {{cx|politics|lang=en}} An organised unit or faction within a larger political organisation.
#: ''a militant '''tendency'''''

